properties.Name: LifeInsurabilityRiskCategory
properties.Description:
A means of categorizing the risk to insure the Policyholder based upon criteria for age, lifestyle, family history and physical condition.

Ex:
- Preferred Risk
- Standard Risk
- Substandard Risk

PREFERRED RISK
A person whose occupation, physical condition, lifestyle or similar characteristic indicates they are a prospect for longevity in that age group.

STANDARD RISK
A person who is, according to the insuring company's underwriting standards, entitled to insurance protection without extra-rating or special restrictions.

SUBSTANDARD RISK
A person who is considered by the insurer's underwriting standards to be an under-average or impaired insurance risk because of some factor:  family medical history, physical condition, disease, occupation, residence location or dangerous habits or pastimes.
